FG-261 — §2112(a) Venue & Consolidation (Pick Your Forum, Then Prove It)
	•	⚖️ Core Message: Multiple petitions trigger §2112(a) consolidation; venue is a race + lottery—plan it.
	•	📖 Lesson Content: File/serve fast; note first-filed circuit; if multiple within 10 days, JPML Clerk runs lottery; move to transfer for convenience/interest-of-justice; keep the same relief text in all circuits.
	•	📝 Assignment: Draft a 7-line §2112 notice/motion identifying first-filed and your transfer factors.
	•	✅ Model Response: “Petitions filed in 9th/D.C.; first-filed 9th; transfer to D.C. promotes uniformity; relief text identical.”
	•	💡 Reflection Summary: One ask, any circuit.
	•	🎨 Visual Concept: Two courthouse icons merging into one “consolidated” stamp.

⸻

FG-262 — §2112 Docketing Pack (Serve Agency • File Statement • Proof)
	•	⚖️ Core Message: Consolidation runs on papered service and statements.
	•	📖 Lesson Content: Same-day service on agency; file a docketing statement (statute/venue/clock/parties); attach proofs (mail/ECF); neutral tone.
	•	📝 Assignment: Build a 1-page docketing statement template with four boxes (Statute • Venue • Clock • Parties).
	•	✅ Model Response: “Statute: §__ ; Venue: D.C. Cir.; Clock: FR pub 08/01 → 60d; Parties: petitioners/intervenors listed.”
	•	💡 Reflection Summary: Clean admin wins early fights.
	•	🎨 Visual Concept: A single form with four labeled boxes.

⸻

FG-263 — Agency Reconsideration While Petition Pending (Two Lanes, One Ask)
	•	⚖️ Core Message: Ask the agency to reconsider while the court retains the petition.
	•	📖 Lesson Content: File agency reconsideration with same relief; move court for limited remand/hold (task/time/scope); status on return; no merits expansion.
	•	📝 Assignment: Draft paired filings: 1-page agency reconsideration + 7-line court motion (hold/limited remand).
	•	✅ Model Response: “Hold 30 days for agency reconsideration on timing harm; status day 21; petition retained.”
	•	💡 Reflection Summary: Two forums, one remedy.
	•	🎨 Visual Concept: A loop arrow from court → agency → court.

⸻

FG-264 — AR Index Disputes (Complete vs. Correct, Not Expand)
	•	⚖️ Core Message: Move to complete/correct the index—don’t add merits.
	•	📖 Lesson Content: Identify missing/ mis-indexed items (ID/page); propose replacement table; attach certified copies; no new evidence; hash the corrected index.
	•	📝 Assignment: Draft a 6-row “missing/mis-indexed” table with proposed fixes and hashes.
	•	✅ Model Response: “Add Method Memo (AR 118:1–12); correct date on AR 204; index PDF SHA-256 ….”
	•	💡 Reflection Summary: Fix the map; leave the terrain.
	•	🎨 Visual Concept: An index page with one red circle and a corrected line.

⸻

FG-265 — Stay Pending Agency Reconsideration (Narrow & Dated)
	•	⚖️ Core Message: Pair a short stay with the agency’s reconsideration window.
	•	📖 Lesson Content: Identify reconsideration task/time; ask for partial §705 stay limited to a paragraph/step; add status and sunset.
	•	📝 Assignment: Draft a 7-line stay motion tied to the agency’s reconsideration schedule.
	•	✅ Model Response: “Stay ¶3 for 30d while agency reconsiders timing harms; status 14d; sunset automatic.”
	•	💡 Reflection Summary: Targeted stays invite yes.
	•	🎨 Visual Concept: A small pause badge attached to one numbered paragraph.

⸻

FG-266 — Remand Without Vacatur (Allied-Signal Factors in One Box)
	•	⚖️ Core Message: If vacatur is disruptive, request remand without vacatur—but write the task.
	•	📖 Lesson Content: Two factors: seriousness of deficiency; disruptive consequences; propose task/time/scope with status; no new merits.
	•	📝 Assignment: Draft a 6-line Allied-Signal paragraph plus a 3-step remand instruction.
	•	✅ Model Response: “Defect: failure to consider timing; disruption high; remand 60d for response; status 30/60; rule otherwise remains.”
	•	💡 Reflection Summary: Cure the step, not the system.
	•	🎨 Visual Concept: A scale labeled “defect/disruption” over a narrow instruction card.

⸻

FG-267 — Intervenor Motions (Stake • Distinct Value • Limits)
	•	⚖️ Core Message: Intervenors must show stake and distinct contribution.
	•	📖 Lesson Content: Statement: why bound by order; non-duplicative topic; page/time caps; align with relief; propose limited participation order.
	•	📝 Assignment: Draft a 7-line intervention motion with one-issue scope.
	•	✅ Model Response: “Stake: compliance burden; Topic: timing data only; 10 pages / 5 min; relief aligned.”
	•	💡 Reflection Summary: Small seats get granted.
	•	🎨 Visual Concept: A narrow chair labeled “Intervenor — Issue 2 only.”

⸻

FG-268 — Comment Preservation (Specificity • Pin • Ask)
	•	⚖️ Core Message: Preserve by making your comment specific and asking for a response.
	•	📖 Lesson Content: Comment lines: specific concern (with data/pin), requested response/analysis, proposed fix; later show “asked/ignored” crosswalk.
	•	📝 Assignment: Write three comment sentences that preserve timing harm precisely.
	•	✅ Model Response: “Explain print-window costs with vendor PO (AR 118:12); respond to timing alternatives; adopt window or justify rejection.”
	•	💡 Reflection Summary: Clear asks force reasoned replies.
	•	🎨 Visual Concept: A comment bubble pointing to a checklist box “Respond.”

⸻

FG-269 — CFR/FR Pin Hygiene (Volume • Page • Capture • Hash)
	•	⚖️ Core Message: Cite rules like evidence—exact and verifiable.
	•	📖 Lesson Content: CFR: title §; FR: volume/page/date; add captured [date] and SHA-256 if you host; source URLs in footnotes, not text.
	•	📝 Assignment: Rewrite two CFR/FR cites with capture/hash lines.
	•	✅ Model Response: “88 Fed. Reg. 12345 (Aug. 1, 2025) (captured 08/19; SHA-256 …); 40 C.F.R. § __.”
	•	💡 Reflection Summary: Exact pins end link fights.
	•	🎨 Visual Concept: A rule page tile with a small fingerprint footer.

⸻

FG-270 — Multi-Forum Coordination (District Case + Petition)
	•	⚖️ Core Message: Don’t let parallel forums undercut each other—align asks and calendars.
	•	📖 Lesson Content: File a coordination letter: what’s pending where; propose hold/limited remand; keep identical relief text; status cadence; neutral tone.
	•	📝 Assignment: Draft a 7-line coordination note listing both captions, dates, and a one-line proposal.
	•	✅ Model Response: “District PI hearing 09/01; D.C. Cir. petition docketed. Proposal: hold district 21d while petition proceeds; status 14d.”
	•	💡 Reflection Summary: One map prevents mixed signals.
	•	🎨 Visual Concept: Two timelines tied by a single bracket labeled “coordination.”